<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-24T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.6176/225: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-24T19:00:00-05:00">April 24,
                                    1934—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>160. Mr. Harvey Firestone<note n="30" xml:id="d527fn30">Chairman of the
                                Board of Directors of the Firestone Tire &amp; Rubber Co.</note>
                            informs the Department that information received from London indicates
                            the rubber restriction agreement will be signed April 28 to enter into
                            effect almost immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>